The US delegation, led by Environmental Protection Agency Administrator Gina McCarthy, will attend the Extraordinary Meeting of the Parties to the Montreal Protocol in Vienna, Austria. The Montreal Protocol is a global agreement aimed at protecting the ozone layer by controlling the production and consumption of ozone-depleting substances. The meeting will discuss a proposed amendment to address the emissions of hydrofluorocarbons, which are potent greenhouse gases contributing to climate change. The US delegation includes representatives from various government departments, including the White House, Department of State, Environmental Protection Agency, and Department of Agriculture.